---
title: Tuna Mayo Rice Bowl
source: https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1023224-tuna-mayo-rice-bowl
tags: lunch
---

In a small bowl, stir @canned tuna{5%oz} (preferably in oil, well drained), @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @toasted sesame oil{1%tsp}, and @soy sauce{1/2%tsp} to combine.

Add @cooked white rice{1%cup} (preferably short- or medium-grain) to a bowl and spoon the tuna mixture on top. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds, furikake, or chopped scallions, if using.
